<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ban2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ban,</orth> vb., to curse; 1) trans.: <cit><quote>--ing his boisterous and unruly beast,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 326" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 326</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1460" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1460</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 25</bibl>.<lb />2) absolutely: <cit><quote>though she strive to try her strength, and b. and brawl,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 318" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 318</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fell --ing hag,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 42</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.319" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 319</bibl> <cit><quote>(curse and b.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.319" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 319</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>upon the --ing shore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 11</bibl></cit> (only in Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi>, the rest of O. Edd. <emph>foaming</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>